n Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hastang","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Norman personal name <i>Hastang</i>, <i>Hastenc</i>, <i>Hasten</i> (Old Norse <i>Hásteinn</i> ‘high’ + ‘stone’). See also   Hastings  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Haston","meanings":["English: habitational name from Haston in Shropshire. The placename probably derives from Old English <i>hēafod</i> ‘head’ + <i>stān</i> ‘stone’.","English: from the Norman personal name <i>Hasten</i>; see   Hasting  .","Scottish: habitational name from Hestan in Rerrick (Kirkcudbrightshire)."]},{"name":"Hastings","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from Hastings (Sussex), near which the English army was defeated by the Normans in 1066. The placename derives from an Old English personal name <i>Hǣsta</i> + the Old English groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i>. In the latter part of the 12th century, at the time of William the Lion, the surname was taken to Scotland, where it assimilated instances of the native Scottish surname <b>Harestane</b>.","English: variant of   Hasting   with Middle English genitival <i>-s</i>.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hOistín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Oistín</i>’, the Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Augustine</i> (see   Austin  )."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John de Hastang was born before 1275, in Chebsey, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Hastings, was 26 and his mother, Isabel Mortimer, was 26. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died before 1332, in Leamington Hastings, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Bef 1275–Bef 1332":"enne 1275–enne 1332","1268–1336":"1268–1336","1275–1332":"1275–1332","1295–1348":"1295–1348","1305–1336":"1305–1336","1249–Male":"1249–Surnud","1248–1292":"1248–1292","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","1292":"1292","10 August 1292":"10. august 1292","1305":"1305","1249":"1249","1348":"1348","1248":"1248","1336":"1336","1268":"1268","Bef 1332":"enne 1332","1332":"1332","Bef 1275":"enne 1275","Arundel, Sussex, England":"Arundel, Sussex, England","Leamington Hastings, Warwickshire, England":"Leamington Hastings, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chebsey, Stafford, England":"Chebsey, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1275–Bef 1332":"ennen vuotta 1275–ennen vuotta 1332","1268–1336":"1268–1336","1275–1332":"1275–1332","1295–1348":"1295–1348","1305–1336":"1305–1336","1249–Male":"1249–Kuollut","1248–1292":"1248–1292","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","1292":"1292","10 August 1292":"10. elokuuta 1292","1305":"1305","1249":"1249","1348":"1348","1248":"1248","1336":"1336","1268":"1268","Bef 1332":"ennen vuotta 1332","1332":"1332","Bef 1275":"ennen vuotta 1275","Arundel, Sussex, England":"Arundel, Sussex, England","Leamington Hastings, Warwickshire, England":"Leamington Hastings, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chebsey, Stafford, England":"Chebsey, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Bef 1275–Bef 1332":"avant 1275–avant 1332","1268–1336":"1268–